# Web Frontend Conventions

## Stack
React 18, Vite, TypeScript (strict), TailwindCSS, Redux Toolkit, React Router DOM.

## File Structure
```
web/src/
  pages/          — Route-level components (one per page)
  components/     — Reusable UI components
  components/ui/  — Primitives (Button, Card, Input, etc.)
  hooks/          — Custom React hooks
  store/          — Redux store, slices
  services/       — Firebase init, API client
  utils/          — Pure helper functions
```

## Component Pattern
```tsx
interface Props {
  hobby: Hobby;
  onSave?: () => void;
}

export const HobbyCard: React.FC<Props> = ({ hobby, onSave }) => {
  // 1. Hooks → 2. State → 3. Effects → 4. Handlers → 5. Return JSX
};
```

## Import Aliases
- `@/` → `web/src/` (configured in vite.config.ts)
- `@shared/` → `shared/`

## State Management
- Global state (user, hobbies, AI) → Redux Toolkit slices
- UI-only state (form inputs, toggles) → `useState`
- Use `useAppDispatch` and `useAppSelector` typed hooks

## Firebase in Frontend
- Firebase SDK is **optional** — the app works in local mode without credentials
- `isFirebaseConfigured` flag in `services/firebase.ts` gates all Firebase calls
- Hooks (`useAuth`, `useHobbyQuiz`, `useHobbyCoach`) must check this flag before calling `httpsCallable`

## Styling
- TailwindCSS utility classes; custom theme in `tailwind.config.js`
- Use `cn()` helper from `utils/cn.ts` for conditional classes
- Font: Outfit (loaded via Google Fonts in `index.html`)

## API Calls
- AI features: `httpsCallable()` to Cloud Functions (requires Firebase Auth)
- CRUD: Axios via `services/api.ts` with `/api` prefix (Vite proxies to backend)
